name: Pete 🔥#CancelRent🔥 Harrison
tweet: This pandemic is going to change our way of life for the short term and the long term. We have a choice about how. And we have the power to make our government fight for people and not profits and for communities over corporations. But you need to step up right now.

name: Pete 🔥#CancelRent🔥 Harrison
tweet: As much as it pains me to say this, it doesn’t have to be on an electoral campaign either. Go find organizations that are fighting in your neighborhood or fighting for issues that directly impact them. They exist and they need your time and energy right now more than ever!

name: Pete 🔥#CancelRent🔥 Harrison
tweet: Doesn’t mean tweeting. It means joining local organizing groups. It means making calls to your elected officials with clear demands and clear threats. It means plugging in with mutual aid groups in your neighborhood to care for each other and to activate more people

name: Pete 🔥#CancelRent🔥 Harrison
tweet: Most people don’t engage in activism; people are busy, tired, disillusioned, whatever.  I get it and understand. But #COVID19 has changed that  You need to fight right now today to make sure our government protects us from the virus and the economic collapse. They haven’t so far

name: Pete 🔥#CancelRent🔥 Harrison
tweet: Right now groups around the country are organizing demands on their local and federal govs to suspend rent, mortgage, utility, debt payments. To release prisoners and house the homeless. To pay workers and small businesses who are suffering. And to make sure people get testing
